gamin
------------------------------------------
Gamin is a file and directory monitoring system defined to be
a subset of the FAM (File Alteration Monitor) system.

 The main goals of the project are:
 1/ minimize the security model of FAM
 2/ simplify the code base
 3/ provide an API and ABI compatible replacement for FAM
 4/ try to fix some other issues like resource consumption

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.25-15
  glib2-2.16.6-1
(python-gamin)
  python-2.5.2-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf2.5-2.63-1
  automake1.10-1.10.1-1
  binutils-20080624-2
  cygport-0.4.2-1
  gawk-3.1.6-1
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  gnome-common-2.24.0-1
  libtool-2.2.6a-1
  make-3.81-1
  pkg-config-0.23a-2
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical website:
  http://www.gnome.org/~veillard/gamin/

Canonical download:
  http://www.gnome.org/~veillard/gamin/sources/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack gamin-0.1.10-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./gamin-0.1.10-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/gamin-0.1.10-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/gamin-0.1.10-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libfam-devel-0.1.10-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libfam0-0.1.10-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libgamin1-devel-0.1.10-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libgamin1_0-0.1.10-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/python-gamin-0.1.10-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary packages:

(gamin)
  /usr/lib/gamin/gam_server.exe
  /usr/share/doc/gamin-0.1.10/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/gamin-0.1.10/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/gamin-0.1.10/COPYRIGHT
  /usr/share/doc/gamin-0.1.10/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/gamin-0.1.10/INSTALL
  /usr/share/doc/gamin-0.1.10/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/gamin-0.1.10/README
  /usr/share/doc/gamin-0.1.10/TODO

(libfam0)
  /usr/bin/cygfam-0.dll

(libfam-devel)
  /usr/include/fam.h
  /usr/lib/libfam.dll.a
  /usr/lib/libfam.la

(libgamin1_0)
  /usr/bin/cyggamin-1-0.dll

(libgamin1-devel)
  /usr/lib/libgamin-1.dll.a
  /usr/lib/libgamin-1.la
  /usr/lib/libgamin_shared.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/gamin.pc

(python-gamin)
  /usr/lib/python2.5/site-packages/_gamin.dll
  /usr/lib/python2.5/site-packages/_gamin.la
  /usr/lib/python2.5/site-packages/gamin.py
  /usr/lib/python2.5/site-packages/gamin.pyc
  /usr/lib/python2.5/site-packages/gamin.pyo

------------------

Port Notes:

----- version 0.1.10-1 -----
Version bump.

----- version 0.1.9-1 -----
Version bump.

----- version 0.1.7-1 -----
Version bump.
Includes an updated patch from the FreeBSD project, and a partial(*)
workaround for FAT drives, originally derived from Corinna Vinschen:
http://www.cygwin.com/ml/cygwin/2006-01/msg00818.html
(*) Errors will still occur if running NT4 on a FAT drive.

----- version 0.1.5-1 -----
Initial release for Cygwin.
Includes code portability patches from the FreeBSD project.
Thanks to Lapo Luchini and Alex Dupre for the code patches.


Cygwin port maintained by:
http://sourceware.org/cygwinports/
